other_tests.findings: Cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) was clear. Tube 1 contained 409 red cells per cubic millimeter and 10 white cells per cubic millimeter; tube 4 contained 244 red cells per cubic millimeter and 9 white cells per cubic millimeter, with 87% lymphocytes, 6% monocytes, 0% neutrophils, and 7% atypical cells. Elevated protein level of 94 mg per deciliter (normal range, 10 to 44) and negative result for herpes simplex virus on PCR.
Showed poor labial control of the food bolus as well as impairment in retraction of the base of the tongue, hyolaryngeal elevation, and laryngeal closure.

Revealed neoplastic cells with immunoreactivity for AE1/AE3 cytokeratins and thyroid transcription factor 1 (TTF-1), consistent with leptomeningeal carcinomatosis due to metastatic spread from a primary lung adenocarcinoma.
